  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then cut your <strong>aubergine[s]</strong> in half lengthways (including the stalks)</p><p>Score the flesh in a criss-cross pattern, taking care not to cut through to the skin, then rub the flesh with a large drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> aubergine half[ves]</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined tray (or two!), cut side up and put in the oven for an initial 20 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
